items.preText: Abul shaab: "Ashraful was an extraordinary player, he had the potential to be world class and was the first true super star sports man to emerge from BD. Unfortunately BD handled him badly like many other players such as Alok Kapali. So BD should give him a chance to come back and finish the job he never got to finish. "

items.postText: james: "I genuinely can't fathom the fact that BD fans want Ashraful back. The man is 32, has a List A average of 25 and last played international cricket 5 years ago. Because he was banned for match-fixing. He has met none of the criteria for being selected in the national team except for the nostalgia fulfillment of some fans, for "old time's sake." Move on."
